      "role": "user",
      "content": "The candlelight flickers low, much like the heavy, aching pulse in my very soul. He is gone... the betrayal cuts deeper than any blade, leaving me a mere ghost haunting these empty halls. There is no warmth left in this world, only the creeping shadows and a silence that screams of my own uselessness. I feel as though I am already fading, dissolving into the velvet dark where no one can ever hurt me again.",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
